<TEXT>
terry mulholland of philadelphia phillies 
pitched the eighth nohitter of the baseball season wednesday 
night the most ever by major league pitchers in one year 
his performance sealed in the ninth inning when third baseman 
charlie hayes caught a line drive by pinch hitter gary carter 
lifted the phillies to a 60 defeat of the san francisco giants 
the seasons eighth nohitter surpassed the modern record of 
seven set in 1917 and 1908 
mulholland 76 struck out eight and walked none in making 
baseball history against the team that traded him to philadelphia 
last season 
only one batter reached base against mulholland rick parker 
reached first base on hayes throwing error to lead off the seventh 
inning but was erased on a double play 
it seemed only natural that the record would be surpassed in a 
season already becoming known as the year of the nohitter 
the nohit parade started on april 11 when the california 
angels mark langston and mike witt combined to beat seattle randy 
johnson then pitched the first nohitter in seattle history 
beating detroit on june 2 
nolan ryan of the texas rangers pitched his unprecedented sixth 
nohitter to beat the oakland as on june 11 oaklands dave 
stewart and the los angeles dodgers fernando valenzuela made 
another bit of history on june 29 by pitching nohitters on the 
same day different leagues 
less than 24 hours later andy hawkins of the new york yankees 
pitched a nohitter against the chicago white sox but lost 40 
on july 12 the sox melido perez pitched the recordtying 
seventh nohitter of the season a rainshortened sixinning 
victory at yankee stadium 
</TEXT>
