<TEXT>
a state agency today put nine homes 
up for sale near the love canal chemical dump and said the 
neighborhood bought up by the government in the 1970s is safe but 
with no guarantees 
the homes have been rigorously tested and are as safe as any in 
niagara falls said william l broderick executive director of the 
love canal area revitalization agency 
but he said it was impossible to guarantee that the toxic 
chemical leaks that once drove 2500 people from the neighborhood 
would not recur 
theres no written guarantees going to be given broderick 
said at a news conference at his agencys offices about 500 feet 
from the site of the toxic dump all we have is the written 
assurance of the state health department and the state 
environmental department as to the maintenance of the canal 
if there is a problem in the future im sure the state will 
come back and do as they did last time 
the agency originally planned to offer 10 homes today but 
broderick said a resident of the neighborhood already had offered 
to buy one 
eight years ago the idea that anyone would want to move back to 
love canal was so preposterous that it became a joke in the movie 
tootsie 
james e carr the agencys planning director said tours of the 
homes will be given for the next 20 days to interested buyers the 
agency plans to start accepting offers sept 5 
broderick said a flurry of lastminute court action on tuesday 
would not prevent the agency from going ahead with plans to sell 
some love canal homes 
more than 200 people including several former residents have 
expressed interest in the small singlefamily homes asking prices 
of 40000 to 60000 about 20 percent less than comparable homes 
elsewhere have stimulated interest 
many prospective buyers say they believe the danger from the 
22000 tons of chemicals still buried there has been overstated 
the canal went right through my back yard as kids we used to 
go back in those fields mow them down play baseball said gail 
mcclinsey im fine and i have two children theyre fine i 
keep in touch with some of the friends i grew up with theyre 
fine 
but doubts remain about allowing people to move into homes just 
a few blocks from the canal bed where hooker chemical co dumped 
dioxin pcbs and other toxic chemicals in the 1940s and 1950s 
leaks discovered in the late 1970s led 2500 residents to 
abandon their homes making love canal a national symbol of the 
threat posed by toxic waste in tootsie dustin hoffmans 
character considers taking a part in a play called return to love 
canal 
carr said the area containing the 10 homes is safe even though 
most of the chemicals dumped in the canal have not been removed 
they do testing all the time theres continual monitoring going 
on he said sure id live there 
richard j lippes a lawyer for environmental and community 
groups seeking to block resettlement disagreed 
i would never buy a home in love canal i would never put my 
family in such jeopardy he said and if i wouldnt do it 
there is no way i could recommend to anyone else to do it 
the groups asked state supreme court justice joseph mintz to 
enforce his 1985 injunction barring resettlement pending 
environmental and livability studies but the agency urged him to 
lift the order saying the studies have been done 
the attorney generals office which originally sought the 
injunction said it would not object we feel that the terms of 
the injunction have been met said leslie gersing spokeswoman 
for attorney general robert abrams 
no rulings are expected until mintz returns from vacation next 
month 
a study completed in 1988 found that the resettlement area north 
and northwest of love canal which contains about 250 singlefamily 
homes was no more contaminated than comparable parts of niagara 
falls an area east of the canal containing about 270 homes was 
deemed uninhabitable because of contamination 
resettlement opponents claim the livability study and an 
environmental review completed this year are flawed among other 
things they say that other areas of niagara falls may be polluted 
from several chemical plants and other toxic dumps 
they havent determined that those control areas are safe and 
if those control areas arent safe neither is love canal lippes 
said 
