committee has contributed to helms reelection campaign 
while economic boycotts may be considered lawful as a means of 
political protest newspaper articles submitted with the 
complaint leave no doubt that the true purpose and intent of 
defendants activities extend beyond acts of protest to the defeat 
of senator jesse helms for reelection says the complaint filed 
last week 
because none of the groups are registered as political 
committees efforts promoting the boycott amount to an improper 
spending of funds to influence an election the complaint alleges 
the complaint names act updistrict of columbia and act upsan 
francisco which are aids activist groups with gay rights 
