<TEXT>
prime minister lothar de maiziere on 
wednesday fired four cabinet ministers who had dealt closely with 
the nations crumbling economy they included the agriculure chief 
who earlier was pelted with eggs by angry farmers 
the fired officials were finance minister walter romberg 
economics minister gerhard pohl justice minister kurt wuensche and 
agriculture minister peter pollack 
hours before de maiziere announced the dismissals pollack tried 
to speak to thousands of protesting farmers on east berlins main 
square he was shouted down with cries of bandit and dog 
