strikes the east german news agency adn said 
officials say other sections of the economy will quickly follow 
the plunging fortunes of the agriculture industry 
experts say up to 4 million of east germanys 88 million 
workers could lose their jobs as the nation continues its move to a 
market economy at an unprecedented pace 
almost 1 million workers now are either jobless or working 
shorter hours at lower pay under a west germanfinanced program to 
keep workers targeted for layoff on the job 
