were realized here are items on watkins list 
boost production from alaskas north slope now 18 million 
barrels daily by 50000 barrels that could be done within 90 
days watkins said 
the department would attempt to mediate a longrunning dispute 
over whether oil from the offshore point arguello fields in 
california should be transported to refinery via pipeline or ship 
chevron oil and santa barbara county authorities welcome mediation 
watkins said if successful it could produce an extra 75000 
barrels a day within six months 
encourage utilities to switch from oil to other fuels even 
those that are more expensive saving 100000 barrels a day this 
could require relaxed environmental regulations 
boost production of naval petroleum reserve fields mainly elk 
hills calif by 5000 barrels a day by october 
ask state regulators to be more flexible in setting 
