pascaltrouillot to abide by the joint governing agreement under 
which the council was to have veto power over her cabinet 
appointments and major decisions 
mrs pascaltrouillots civilian caretaker government came to 
power march 13 after a weeklong popular uprising toppled military 
ruler lt gen prosper avril 
mrs pascaltrouillot 46 a former supreme court justice 
became the first female president in haitis 186year history 
at the time she agreed to govern alongside the council of 
state whose members were appointed by civilian opposition leaders 
until after the countrys first free elections could take place 
later in the year 
the council is comprised of representatives of civic 
organizations and provincial districts 
the conflict between the council and mrs pascaltrouillot came 
to a head may 21 when the president appointed marie violene 
legagneur as finance minister without the councils authorization 
council members regarded legagneur as a sympathizer of the 
duvalier family dictatorship of jeanclaude baby doc duvalier 
who fled into exile in 1986 and of his late father francois 
papa doc 
