of failing to implement the administrative judicial military and 
economic reforms that were set down as prerequisites for genuine 
elections when the caretaker government came to power 
haitis last attempt at holding free elections ended in failure 
on nov 29 1987 thugs in collusion with the army killed at 
least 34 voters at the polls halting the first free general 
elections in haiti since independence from france in 1804 
