use of force a couple of days ago but that the directive had 
gone through a rigorous intraagency approval process 
departments such as state and commerce were brought into the 
process because of the delicate nature involved in dealing with a 
situation where shipments might be carried by ships flagged by 
third countries 
a preliminary message was sent out to commanders late wednesday 
but was pulled back for revision and the formal final directive was 
scheduled to be sent to the fleet early thursday the source said 
