iraqs saddam hussein in a move that 
could free military manpower and ease the stranglehold of economic 
sanctions offered wednesday to make peace with his longtime enemy 
iran 
iran greeted the proposal with optimism but said a thorough 
study was needed that countrys islamic republic news agency said 
president hashemi rafsanjani and his cabinet were meeting to 
discuss the proposal 
iran and iraq never formally settled their eightyear war 
although it ended with a ceasefire in august 1988 
in his proposal the iraqi leader said he would pull troops out 
of territories seized from iran and free iranian prisoners of war 
he also suggested he was relinquishing the iraqi claim to full 
control of the strategic shattalarab waterway to the persian gulf 
those were major points of disagreement that stalled peace talks 
almost from the time they began five days after the 1988 
ceasefire 
in addition iraq allowed iranians trapped by the invasion of 
kuwait to leave irans official islamic republic news agency said 
