<TEXT>
three former northwest airlines pilots used 
an alice in wonderland defense at their trial on charges they 
flew while drunk a federal prosecutor said wednesday in closing 
arguments 
assistant us attorney elizabeth de la vega said the defense 
attempted to make a routine flight look difficult and at one point 
contended it was easier to fly during an emergency 
she said the pilots also told of being sober when common sense 
and bloodalcohol tests showed obvious impairment 
it tells you a lot about the defense in this case it sounds 
like alice in wonderland de la vega told the us district court 
jury they say its hard to fly if its easy but its easy to 
fly if its an emergency 
william mauzy attorney for first officer robert kirchner said 
