nd to minneapolis in tests about two hours after the flight 
kirchners bloodalcohol was 006 percent balzers 008 percent 
and prouse 013 percent in many states the legal limit for driving 
a car is 010 percent 
the case marks the us justice departments first prosecution 
under a 1988 federal law prohibiting operation of a common carrier 
while under the influence 
the law doesnt specify an illegal bloodalcohol content to 
find the aviators guilty jurors must conclude they were impaired 
by alcohol even though there were no problems with the flight 
