<DOCNO> AP900815-0118 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
matching marrow is a threestep process first the blood is 
tested to classify its first four antigens or cell identifiers 
that costs 75 per donor the second step is to identify the last 
two antigens that costs about 300 if all six match a final test 
mixes the patients and donors blood to see if one rejects the 
other 
because of the cost the second step called dr typing 
usually is not done until a match is achieved on the first four 
antigens only about 30 percent of nationals donors for example 
have had dr typing 
on june 1 lifesavers staff followed up on potential marrow 
donors whose names had been submitted to national as far back as 
march in two days the staff members claimed they located 62 
potential donors who had not yet been contacted by national for 
followup tests 
national responds that it sometimes has trouble locating donors 
after a potential match is found and the registry says some 
patients with common blood types can be matched preliminarily to 
scores of donors national says it cant test each of those matches 
immediately due to the logistics and high cost 
for its part national said it wants to do away with 
lifesavers publicity techniques featuring poignant pleas for 
donors by patients and their families instead it will seek donors 
to contribute marrow and money through corporations and service 
organizations 
quam said lifesavers in essence told families how much money 
had to be raised we dont want these determined moms and dads to 
feel so much pressure they have to second mortgage their homes 
plead with relatives or cash in iras she said 
leaders of each registry include people who got involved because 
of the illness of a family member or friend and those emotional 
ties color the debate over what approach to use 
those same emotions are at work among those who want to 
reorganize a system that is not working 
im concerned because it isnt a cohesive system because its 
too much of a burden on families said mrs lundquist the widow 
whose husbands match came too late im concerned that lives are 
being lost because of an inadequate system 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
