the search for a bonemarrow transplant for 
peter lundquist dragged on for months it was more time than he had 
lundquist 37 a miami television news anchor and father of 
three died of lymphoma in february a week after potential donors 
were found 
his wife bonnie says administrative delays in a boggeddown 
system robbed her husband of precious time 
lundquist wanted others to have the chance that eluded him 
before he died he extracted some pretty stringent promises 
from his wife to help other patients and better the system 
peter was a really giving person who cared about other 
people mrs lundquist said in a telephone interview he left 
those good qualities i tried to step in where he had to leave 
off 
mrs lundquist promotes marrow donation because patients have 
no other options its the only system we have right now 
but she wants lawmakers and the public to know that 
the bureaucracy needs to be speeded up lundquist was orking 
through a transplant center in august his doctor asked the center 
to authorize a search with the nations biggest donor bank the 
search wasnt begun until november later there were delays in 
processing potential matches 
