<TEXT>
from the outside next computers 
nondescript white factory building could be mistaken for an 
insurance company claims office 
inside it looks more like a showroom for italian furniture 
next chairman steve jobs fascination with detail and design is 
evident everywhere from the slick blackandwhite decor to the two 
varieties of gourmet coffee in the employee lunchroom 
a glass wall behind the reception area reveals the buildings 
true purpose through it the companys highly automated assembly 
line can be glimpsed below 
the assembly floor is surprisingly small about the size of a 
couple of football fields on a recent visit it also was 
surprisingly quiet the assembly line was not running and little 
activity was evident among the handful of workers hardly a good 
sign for jobs startup company 
the idle assembly line and operatingroom cleanliness gave the 
plant situated in a wellmanicured office park the air of a 
science fair project 
but randy heffner nexts vice president of manufacturing said 
it is unusual for a startup computer company to have its own plant 
in the first place most would farm out production until sales 
increased to a level to justify the expenditure on machinery 
by building its own plant heffner said next can control the 
quality of its products reduce inventory cut retooling costs and 
be more responsive to customer needs 
he said the plant currently is operating at onethird capacity 
but he would not say what that figure is jobs has said the plant 
can support sales of 1 billion a year 
of the 50 employees at the factory only nine are needed to run 
the customdesigned robotic assembly line which next says is one 
of the most advanced in the world the rest work in packaging 
shipping and other areas 
because the company has its own assembly line it can put 
together its own prototype computer circuit boards to make sure 
there will be no unforeseen problems in production that may not be 
evident in the design phase said heffner who worked at computer 
giant hewlettpackard co before joining next 
in addition it can produce a prototype board for nexts 
engineers in a few days instead of the few weeks if production 
were contracted out he said 
about 20 revisions were made in the circuit board used in the 
next machine he said 
