a reorganization plan for the letteringmachine 
maker kroy inc and a european subsidiary has been confirmed by a 
us bankruptcy court judge 
under the plan approved by judge robert mooreman more than 19 
billion in liabilities will be eliminated and minneapolisbased red 
oak investment corp will provide operating funds 
confirmation of the plan provides sufficient working capital 
to enable kroy to continue to expand its operation and products 
and it preserves the jobs of our nearly 300 employees said kroy 
president howard klemmer 
kroy and kroy europe ltd were sold in 1986 to a management 
group and an employee stock ownership plan esop in a leveraged 
buyout 
kroy was unable to repay the 60 million debt incurred in the 
buyout and the company filed for reorganization may 15 under 
chapter 11 of the federal bankruptcy code assets of 50 million 
and liabilities of 53 million were listed on the bankruptcy 
petition 
during the confirmation hearing it was announced that the 
company had reached a settlement with the us department of labor 
and valley national bank of arizona trustee of the esop in a 
355 million lawsuit the labor department had sued kroy for 
hurting the esop with the buyout 
as part of the settlement the labor department has agreed to 
dismiss kroy from the lawsuit 
