<TEXT>
evoking images of boardroom napoleons french 
executives have struck out beyond their borders to wage the most 
aggressive corporate takeover campaign in europe 
the conquests extend far beyond the continent goodrich tires 
mack trucks and maalox antacid are among the american products 
french companies are commandeering in a transatlantic offensive 
even napoleon would envy 
some experts say france after decades of passive and insular 
business practices is simply catching up girding itself for a 
single european market by doing now what corporations from other 
economic powers have done for years 
but there is no disagreement that the french have undertaken the 
process with skill enthusiasm vast reserves of cash and the 
strong encouragement of their government 
that encouragement has prompted some complaints arising from 
the fact that many of the acquisitive french companies are 
stateowned 
european deal review published by the us consultancy group 
translink said there were 40 french state acquisitions of european 
targets in 1989 valued at 334 billion 
france is in effect nationalizing europe said mark dixon 
the reviews editor 
many governments consider such takeovers unfair because of the 
protection given to the french companies by their own government 
european community officials recently ordered renault and other 
french companies to pay back hundreds of millions of dollars of 
state aid which was ruled to give them an unfair advantage over 
companies from other ec members 
britain the most popular target for french companies last year 
said it may adopt special measures to prevent statebacked 
takeovers 
the sunday times of london in a recent fullpage article titled 
france inc storms the barricades said many experts see the 
hidden hand of the french government behind the sudden aggression 
of french dealmakers who for the first time have overtaken the 
british as europes most acquisitive businessmen 
in july alone french companies announced a series of ambitious 
farflung acquisitions including financier bernard tapies 
headlinemaking purchase of an 80 percent interest in adidas the 
west germanbased sporting goods giant 
in other transactions last month 
accor became the worlds largest operator of hotel rooms with 
160000 worldwide by purchasing motel 6 of the united states 
accors owners described their firm as the mcdonalds of the hotel 
world after adding 554 budget motels to a network that already 
included 850 hotels and 3000 restaurants in 60 countries 
lafarge coppee became europes largest cement producer by 
acquiring veb karsdorf a major east german company 
stateowned usinor sacilor announced plans to acquire edgcomb 
corp a major us steel trading company usinor sacilor became 
the worlds secondbiggest steel producer in 1989 through an 
aggressive foreign expansion 
usinor reflects the imperialistic style that appears to be in 
vogue in france said peter dupont a steel industry analyst with 
ubsphillips amp drew ltd in london 
the neonapoleonic trend is slightly anachronistic in terms of 
todays conventional wisdom he said but its in line with the 
tendency of french governments to allow industrial policy to be 
influenced by ideas of national prestige 
olivier collette a frenchman who directs the marketing 
information section at the us embassy in paris said most french 
companies are viewed favorably in the united states as productive 
industrial investors rather than speculators 
ive not detected any reaction similar to those concerning the 
japanese he said noting the french firms were rarely seeking 
real estate investments 
france was probably the last starter in this race collette 
said three years ago of the hundred largest french groups you 
had a very significant portion with very limited operations in the 
united states or none now most of them have a significant 
foothold in the us market 
he said french investment in the united states is now roughly 
equal to us investment in france 
earlier this month us regulators approved the 18 billion 
merger of norton co a massachusettsbased abrasives company with 
saint gobain of paris one of the worlds leading glass 
manufacturers 
when saint gobain proposed the merger in march to help norton 
avert a hostile takeover by a british firm it won praise from the 
us management 
with saint gobain as a partner we will continue to be who we 
are said nortons chairman john nelson 
another aggressive investor in the us market has been 
stateowned chemical company rhonepoulenc it acquired a majority 
interest this year in the pennsylvaniabased rorer group 
bestknown as the maker of maalox antacid thereby forming one of 
the worlds top 10 pharmaceutical companies 
earlier the michelin tire company acquired uniroyalgoodrich 
and pechiney a major packaging manufacturer bought american 
national can renault is in the process of buying mack trucks 
on the other hand the french can show a different side when 
foreign acquirers come calling for example italian financier 
giancarlo parretti tried to buy frances pathecinema film company 
this year but the government blocked the transaction on grounds it 
was not in frances national interest 
its not as easy for foreign companies to make acquisitions in 
france said ian fisher of the mmg patricof a british buyout 
firm the french are much more protective of their 
shareholdings 
why the sudden surge of french acquisitions experts say it 
results partly from french corporate fear of vulnerability in 1992 
when western europe is to be melded into a single market 
french industries are realizing that if they are going to 
compete in the new europe theyre going to have to get out there 
and do it said eammon bates head of the brussels office of 
bernard krief consultants 
in the past he said french companies got along satisfactorily 
by serving their large domestic market often with generous 
government support 
now they may find their own markets at home are threatened by 
the single market french industry has to defend its own 
interests bates said 
the best defense france decided was to take the offensive 
companies fortified by frances prosperous economy set out on 
concerted acquisition campaigns to gain large chunks of business 
elsewhere 
france at the highest levels has looked at the strategic 
aspects of 1992 from a fairly partisan angle if we exploit this 
to the full we can ensure further french preeminence in the ec 
bates said 
end adv for sunday aug 19 
